Competition Results — NeurIPS 2025 EEG Challenge
This repository contains our submission to the 2025 NeurIPS EEG Challenge, a competition with 1,183 participating teams and over 8,000 submissions on CodaBench.

Challenge 1 (warm-up phase): Ranked 3rd out of all participants
Challenge 2 (final phase): Ranked 9th



Model versions:
V1: Baseline CBraMod with depthwise Conv2d positional encoding, Hann window + LayerNorm preprocessing, and simple magnitude+phase spectral projection. Shallow encoder (12 layers).
V2: Deepened encoder to 24 layers and upgraded weight initialization to trunc_normal for linear layers. Otherwise identical architecture to V1.
V3: Replaced depthwise Conv2d positional encoding with channel self-attention, enabling the model to learn inter-channel relationships. Switched spectral projection to explicit 51-bin rFFT (magnitude + phase).
V4: Introduced EnhancedSpectralProjection with learnable EEG frequency band weights (Delta/Theta/Alpha/Beta/Gamma), PSD features, and separate mag/phase/power projections. Added gated spectral fusion (spectral_gate) and replaced zero mask encoding with a learned mask_token. Preprocessing switched from Hann window to MAD-based robust standardization for better cross-subject generalization.
V5: Used EnhancedSpectralProjection without spectral gate. Increased attention heads to 10 in the encoder.
V6: Added learnable temporal_pos_encoding to explicitly encode patch position in time. Replaced robust standardization with patch-level LayerNorm (time_norm). Retains gated spectral fusion and channel self-attention from V4.
